desc_batch_group: Execute tasks within the batch processing body by setting the number of batch runs and logic.
tip_parallel_count: Maximum number of parallel executions, up to 10 at a time.
tip_max_execution_count: Total number of batch executions does not exceed this limit. When exceeded, it will directly proceed to the next node.
tip_execution_array: Variables to be used by nodes within the batch processing body. Only supports referencing arrays. The number of loops equals the length of the array, and it will output individual arrays sequentially during execution.
tip_output: Content to be output after the loop completes. Only supports referencing output variables from nodes within the loop. The output content will be automatically assembled into an array type.
msg_fill_execution_array: Please fill in the execution array
